acceptance_criteria: Checked-in inventory (docs/ or item body) maps every CLI command to core modules + identifies business logic embedded in command handlers; each promotion task (item-lifecycle/query/annotations/governance/schema-config) gets its exact function list; findings recorded as notes on pm-usfg
parent: pm-usfg
risk: low
confidence: high
resolution: "Added docs/SDK_PRIMITIVE_INVENTORY.md with a checked-in CLI/MCP-to-SDK primitive inventory, current import-boundary baseline, command-family promotion lanes, and ratchet workflow for moving private core access behind SDK primitives."
expected_result: "Agents have an explicit, low-context inventory for SDK-first promotion work and can choose future primitive lanes without re-discovering the current CLI/MCP core coupling."
actual_result: Inventory document now maps command families to SDK promotion lanes and records the current 101-file boundary scan / 857-edge private core baseline used by the static ratchet gate.
