  "2026-07-05T05:16:12.341Z",claude-code-agent,"Implementation start: live orientation complete. Pairing pm-lodl with pm-8778 in one SDK-first architecture PR because the inventory baseline is the input to the import-boundary ratchet. External checks at start: no open PRs; GH issue #427 remains open for Windows nightly confirmation; Dependabot and CodeQL open alerts are empty; pnpm audit has no known vulnerabilities; pm-changelog latest npm package is pm-changelog@2026.6.30."
  "2026-07-05T05:51:00.434Z",claude-code-agent,"Evidence: added docs/SDK_PRIMITIVE_INVENTORY.md as the checked-in SDK-first command-family inventory for parent pm-usfg. It records the current boundary baseline, maps command families to SDK promotion lanes (lifecycle, query/read, annotations/links, schema/config/profile/init, governance/maintenance, history, plan, execution/diagnostics), and documents the ratchet workflow for reducing private src/core imports as primitives move into src/sdk. Verification passed: pm linked typecheck, full coverage 263 files / 5411 tests at 100/100/100/100, pnpm lint, docs/skills gate, and isolated temp-project dogfood."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-05T05:10:02.572Z",maintainer-agent,"Audit 2026-07-05 (second pass): promotion partition now has 8 families (pm-98cz lifecycle, pm-rjqr reads, pm-zwpp facets+append, pm-oxrw governance, pm-3mna workspace config, pm-4a7m history maintenance, pm-je50 plan, pm-oslr execution/diagnostics). This inventory's deliverable should confirm every command's core calls land in exactly one family, and flag any remainder as new promotion items."
